</claim>
<claim id="CLM-00022">
<claim-text><highlight><bold>22</bold></highlight>. A nucleic acid construct in which a pollen-specific promoter or an ovule-specific promoter is operably linked to a suicide gene selected from the group consisting of barnase, tasselseed2 and diphtheria toxin A gene; wherein said promoter and said suicide gene combination is linked to a transposon, wherein said transposon comprises a selectable marker selected from the group consisting of a gene coding for herbicide resistance, antibiotic resistance, insecticide resistance, nitrogen fixation, improved nutrition and cellulose content. </claim-text>
</claim>
